/* Display dimension: cable attribution. */
"Your %@ can run %@, which needs about %@, but the link is currently carrying about %@ (%@). The video is tunneled over Thunderbolt or USB4, so the cable carries far more than the display needs: this is unlikely to be the cable. It's most likely the resolution or refresh rate selected in Display settings, or this Mac's limit for this display." = "您的 %@ 可支援 %@，約需 %@，但目前連線僅承載約 %@（%@）。由於影像是透過 Thunderbolt 或 USB4 隧道傳輸，線材可提供的頻寬遠高於顯示器需求，因此問題不太可能出在線材。更可能是「顯示器」設定中的解析度或更新率選項，或是這台 Mac 對此顯示器的限制。";
"Your %@ can run %@, which needs about %@, but the link is currently carrying about %@ (%@). The cable is already carrying every DisplayPort lane this Mac provides, so this is unlikely to be the cable. It's most likely the resolution or refresh rate selected in Display settings." = "您的 %@ 可支援 %@，約需 %@，但目前連線僅承載約 %@（%@）。線材已使用這台 Mac 提供的所有 DisplayPort 通道，因此問題不太可能出在線材。更可能是「顯示器」設定中的解析度或更新率選項。";

/* Display dimension: branch device. */
"Your %@ is reached through a USB-C to %@ adapter that reports as %@, currently carrying about %@ (%@), short of the monitor's top mode (%@, about %@). With an adapter in the chain, the adapter's own limit may be the cap rather than the cable. A native DisplayPort connection, or a higher-spec adapter, would tell you which." = "您的 %@ 是透過 USB-C 轉 %@ 轉接器連接，該轉接器回報為 %@。目前約承載 %@（%@），尚未達到顯示器的最高模式（%@，約需 %@）。在有轉接器的情況下，限制因素可能是轉接器本身，而非線材。改用原生 DisplayPort 連接，或使用規格更高的轉接器，有助於判斷原因。";

/* Billboard device (display dimension). */
"Billboard device present" = "偵測到 Billboard 裝置";
"A Billboard device is present on this port. That usually appears when an Alt Mode like DisplayPort was set up but didn't fully come up. Your display is below its best mode, so a re-plug, a different cable, or a different adapter may bring it up. Some docks show a Billboard device normally, so this isn't always a fault." = "此連接埠偵測到 Billboard 裝置。這通常表示 DisplayPort 等 Alt Mode 雖已開始設定，但未能完全啟用。您的顯示器目前未達最佳模式，重新插拔、改用其它線材，或更換轉接器可能有助於恢復正常。有些 Dock 本來就會顯示 Billboard 裝置，因此這不一定代表故障。";

/* Display dimension: compression at the link ceiling (issue #246). */
"Display may be using compression to reach its top mode" = "顯示器可能透過壓縮來達到最高模式";
"Your %@ can run %@, which uncompressed would need about %@. This link is already running every lane at a high rate, carrying about %@ (%@). Many high-resolution displays use compression (DSC) to fit their top mode through a link like this, so the link rate alone can't tell whether you're already at your best mode. If the picture looks right, it most likely is." = "您的 %@ 可支援 %@，若不使用壓縮約需 %@。目前連線已讓所有 lanes 以高速運作，承載約 %@（%@）。許多高解析度顯示器會使用影像串流壓縮（DSC），讓最高模式能透過這類連線傳輸，因此僅憑連線速率無法判斷是否已達到最佳模式。若畫面顯示正常，那麼很可能已經達到最佳模式。";

